1
00:00:15,467 --> 00:00:16,300
<i> Sir. Sir!</i>

2
00:00:16,433 --> 00:00:17,700
<i> I just lost my balance.</i>

3
00:00:17,833 --> 00:00:19,500
<i> Thank you so, so much.</i>

4
00:00:19,633 --> 00:00:21,233
<i> Don't mention it.</i>

5
00:00:21,367 --> 00:00:24,267
<i>Sir Manuel's safety
is my responsibility.</i>

6
00:00:24,400 --> 00:00:26,367
<i> What if Manuel actually died?</i>

7
00:00:26,500 --> 00:00:27,700
<i> Do you still love him?</i>

8
00:00:27,833 --> 00:00:29,100
<i>Is that why you're so concerned?</i>

9
00:00:29,233 --> 00:00:31,133
<i> All I'm saying is,</i>

10
00:00:31,267 --> 00:00:32,800
<i>you should've hurt
the children first.</i>

11
00:00:32,933 --> 00:00:34,233
<i> We lost a child.</i>

12
00:00:34,400 --> 00:00:36,167
<i>They should be the ones
you're taking revenge on.</i>

13
00:00:36,300 --> 00:00:37,800
<i>Oh, thank you so much,
by the way.</i>

14
00:00:37,933 --> 00:00:41,133
<i>Mom and Dad have improved
so much because of you.</i>

15
00:00:41,267 --> 00:00:42,667
<i> Oh, it's nothing.</i>

16
00:00:43,900 --> 00:00:44,733
<i> Jessica?</i>

17
00:00:44,867 --> 00:00:46,567
<i>Do you know our youngest sister?</i>

18
00:00:46,700 --> 00:00:48,467
<i>Sir Manuel mentioned her to me.</i>

19
00:00:48,600 --> 00:00:50,367
<i>It's a shame
you never got to meet her.</i>

20
00:00:50,500 --> 00:00:51,800
<i> She was very kind.</i>

21
00:00:51,933 --> 00:00:54,067
<i>Losing a child is hard,
isn't it, Sir?</i>

22
00:00:54,200 --> 00:00:55,900
<i> Very.</i>

23
00:00:56,033 --> 00:00:58,133
<i> She was far too young to die.</i>

24
00:00:58,267 --> 00:01:00,867
<i>I still had so many plans
for her.</i>

25
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:03,833
<i>You know, I loved
my youngest so much.</i>

26
00:01:03,967 --> 00:01:05,200
<i> I'm confused, Hazel.</i>

27
00:01:05,333 --> 00:01:07,500
<i>I hate Manuel, Felma,
and their children so much.</i>

28
00:01:07,667 --> 00:01:08,933
<i> But they seem fine.</i>

29
00:01:09,067 --> 00:01:11,200
<i>That family
is good at pretending.</i>

30
00:01:11,333 --> 00:01:12,333
<i> But from what I saw,</i>

31
00:01:12,467 --> 00:01:14,333
<i>Manuel seemed
to have really loved Jessica.</i>

32
00:01:14,467 --> 00:01:16,167
<i> Maybe it would be better if...</i>

33
00:01:16,300 --> 00:01:17,833
<i> you didn't go through</i>

34
00:01:18,633 --> 00:01:19,933
<i>with your plan
to take revenge for Jessica.</i>

35
00:01:20,067 --> 00:01:22,100
<i> Our child is gone anyway.</i>

36
00:01:22,933 --> 00:01:24,100
<i> She's dead.</i>

37
00:01:24,233 --> 00:01:25,267
<i> No.</i>

38
00:01:25,933 --> 00:01:27,167
<i> I've already started this.</i>

39
00:01:27,300 --> 00:01:29,200
<i> I'm going to finish it.</i>

40
00:01:32,967 --> 00:01:33,733
But...

41
00:01:34,667 --> 00:01:35,833
maybe...

42
00:01:38,100 --> 00:01:40,300
you might end up
falling for their lies again.

43
00:01:41,967 --> 00:01:43,800
Look what happened to you.

44
00:01:45,200 --> 00:01:47,800
You've only been
to their house once,

45
00:01:49,600 --> 00:01:52,300
and they already convinced you
they're good people.

46
00:01:53,700 --> 00:01:54,667
No, Hazel.

47
00:01:56,300 --> 00:01:58,100
I won't believe them.

48
00:01:59,200 --> 00:02:02,967
I won't believe
anything they say.

49
00:02:11,400 --> 00:02:13,500
- There. Go on, Mom.
- Thank you.

50
00:02:14,900 --> 00:02:18,100
- Merry Christmas, everyone!
- Uncle Noah!

51
00:02:18,233 --> 00:02:20,433
- Where are they?
- Noah.

52
00:02:20,567 --> 00:02:21,667
Thank you for coming.

53
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:23,800
- Merry Christmas.
- Merry Christmas.

54
00:02:23,933 --> 00:02:25,833
Hey! Jojo, come in. Come on.

55
00:02:25,967 --> 00:02:27,433
Jojo!

56
00:02:27,567 --> 00:02:29,133
Merry Christmas.

57
00:02:29,267 --> 00:02:30,433
Jojo!

58
00:02:30,567 --> 00:02:33,200
Jojo, I'm back from outer space.

59
00:02:34,233 --> 00:02:37,133
I look beautiful when
I'm not in my uniform, right?

60
00:02:39,833 --> 00:02:41,133
This is fun.

61
00:02:41,267 --> 00:02:43,900
There are so many of us.

62
00:02:44,033 --> 00:02:45,367
Come on, let's eat.

63
00:02:45,500 --> 00:02:46,533
Wait.

64
00:02:46,667 --> 00:02:49,167
Coleen, lead the prayer.

65
00:02:49,333 --> 00:02:50,400
Sure, Dad.

66
00:02:51,333 --> 00:02:54,467
Let's all close our eyes and
feel the presence of the Lord.

67
00:02:55,833 --> 00:02:58,000
Happy birthday, Jesus.

68
00:02:58,533 --> 00:03:02,100
Thank you for all the blessings
you've given our family.

69
00:03:02,233 --> 00:03:05,833
Thank you also for letting Dad
be with us again.

70
00:03:06,633 --> 00:03:08,900
And we also thank you for
even letting Jessica be with us

71
00:03:09,967 --> 00:03:13,100
for a short moment.

72
00:03:14,467 --> 00:03:18,533
Lord, thank you
because Dad can walk again now.

73
00:03:18,667 --> 00:03:20,067
And Mom...

74
00:03:21,067 --> 00:03:24,000
has survived the tumor
and is recovering.

75
00:03:24,133 --> 00:03:27,567
Thank you for all the food
on our table.

76
00:03:27,700 --> 00:03:28,933
And thank you in advance

77
00:03:29,067 --> 00:03:31,200
for all the blessings
you will still give us.

78
00:03:32,133 --> 00:03:33,167
In Jesus name...

79
00:03:33,300 --> 00:03:34,700
Amen!

80
00:03:34,833 --> 00:03:37,600
- Merry Christmas!
- Merry Christmas!

81
00:03:37,733 --> 00:03:38,900
Merry Christmas!

82
00:03:39,033 --> 00:03:40,733
Come on, let's eat!

83
00:03:40,867 --> 00:03:41,867
- Go on, let's all sit down.
- Jojo!

84
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:43,400
Come on, sit here.

85
00:03:43,533 --> 00:03:45,333
- Yeah.
- Dig in!

86
00:03:46,767 --> 00:03:47,967
Oh, sorry, Dad.

87
00:03:48,100 --> 00:03:49,633
Let's start eating!

88
00:03:50,600 --> 00:03:51,500
There you go.

89
00:03:51,633 --> 00:03:53,933
Would you like some
Lumpiang Shanghai?

90
00:03:54,100 --> 00:03:55,333
Jojo, try the Shanghai.

91
00:03:55,467 --> 00:03:56,367
There.

92
00:03:56,500 --> 00:03:57,833
Jojo, Shanghai.

93
00:03:57,967 --> 00:04:00,800
Here you go.

94
00:04:00,933 --> 00:04:02,033
You're so mean!

95
00:04:02,167 --> 00:04:03,833
- Spaghetti.
- There's also Menudo.

96
00:04:03,967 --> 00:04:04,767
Dad, here.

97
00:04:04,900 --> 00:04:06,267
Ma'am, would you
like some cheese?

98
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:09,567
- Cheese?
- That's good, bro.

99
00:04:26,400 --> 00:04:28,200
- Wow, shorts!
- Thank you, Uncle Noah!

100
00:04:28,367 --> 00:04:30,300
Hey, I like this!

101
00:04:31,467 --> 00:04:32,767
This is my size.

102
00:04:32,900 --> 00:04:34,833
Thank you, Uncle.

103
00:04:34,967 --> 00:04:37,367
- What's that?
- Oh, wow!

104
00:04:38,300 --> 00:04:39,833
I think this
should be in the room.

105
00:04:40,933 --> 00:04:42,233
Nice.

106
00:04:42,367 --> 00:04:43,767
What is it?

107
00:04:43,900 --> 00:04:45,167
This is perfect.

108
00:04:45,300 --> 00:04:46,333
Jojo.

109
00:04:47,633 --> 00:04:48,933
Come here.

110
00:04:53,133 --> 00:04:54,567
Join us.

111
00:04:56,033 --> 00:04:57,067
I'm embarrassed.

112
00:04:57,200 --> 00:04:59,400
I didn't bring any gifts.

113
00:04:59,533 --> 00:05:01,033
Gift doesn't matter.

114
00:05:01,200 --> 00:05:02,900
It's just a material thing.

115
00:05:03,033 --> 00:05:05,400
What matters is your presence.

116
00:05:06,600 --> 00:05:07,467
Thank you.

117
00:05:17,900 --> 00:05:19,400
I love you, Dad!

118
00:05:19,533 --> 00:05:21,067
I love you, I love you,
I love you!

119
00:05:21,200 --> 00:05:22,967
Merry Christmas!

120
00:05:24,833 --> 00:05:25,767
Dad,

121
00:05:26,700 --> 00:05:28,300
I miss you so much.

122
00:05:28,967 --> 00:05:30,067
All of you.

123
00:05:30,867 --> 00:05:32,267
My Pretty Mom,

124
00:05:32,967 --> 00:05:36,167
Handsome Dad,
Good-looking Dad,

125
00:05:36,333 --> 00:05:38,133
Auntie Andrea,

126
00:05:38,267 --> 00:05:39,367
Auntie Coleen,

127
00:05:39,733 --> 00:05:43,433
- Didang...
- Yes! She mentioned me!

128
00:05:43,567 --> 00:05:45,300
Niece, how are you doing there?

129
00:05:45,433 --> 00:05:47,500
Tetay, we miss you so much.

130
00:05:47,633 --> 00:05:48,900
Come home, please.

131
00:05:49,033 --> 00:05:52,933
Princess, come home now.

132
00:05:53,067 --> 00:05:55,000
I love you, my grandchild.

133
00:05:55,133 --> 00:05:57,100
Tetay! How are you?

134
00:05:57,233 --> 00:05:58,167
Hello!

135
00:05:58,300 --> 00:05:59,933
Tetay, you look so beautiful!

136
00:06:00,067 --> 00:06:01,733
Can the dad talk with her first?

137
00:06:01,867 --> 00:06:03,267
It's been a while since
I talked to my daughter!

138
00:06:03,400 --> 00:06:04,267
Let me have my turn.

139
00:06:04,400 --> 00:06:05,167
Go on, go on.

140
00:06:05,300 --> 00:06:07,433
Let them talk.

141
00:06:10,800 --> 00:06:12,700
Sweetie, I'm glad you called.

142
00:06:14,367 --> 00:06:17,067
I've been trying to locate you
in Australia.

143
00:06:17,200 --> 00:06:18,733
Because I want to come see you.

144
00:06:18,867 --> 00:06:20,233
Go, Dad.

145
00:06:20,733 --> 00:06:22,267
Come here.

146
00:06:22,633 --> 00:06:24,367
I'll send you our address.

147
00:06:24,500 --> 00:06:25,900
Really?

148
00:06:27,367 --> 00:06:28,267
Mom.

149
00:06:28,767 --> 00:06:30,367
Sweetie, your mom might get mad.

150
00:06:30,867 --> 00:06:32,667
Do I have the right
to get mad, Jeff?

151
00:06:34,633 --> 00:06:36,500
I'm the one who did you wrong.

152
00:06:37,633 --> 00:06:39,567
I left you without a word.

153
00:06:40,400 --> 00:06:42,267
I took Tetay away from you.

154
00:06:43,400 --> 00:06:44,767
I want to see you soon.

155
00:06:44,900 --> 00:06:46,800
I want to see you and Tetay.

156
00:06:47,967 --> 00:06:51,200
I want to see you, too.
To personally apologize to you.

157
00:06:52,233 --> 00:06:56,133
Dad, come here, please?

158
00:06:56,267 --> 00:06:58,133
I really miss you so much.

159
00:07:00,033 --> 00:07:03,100
Mom misses you, too.
She just doesn't show it.

160
00:07:03,233 --> 00:07:04,700
Come on, Tetay.

161
00:07:04,833 --> 00:07:05,867
Right, Mom?

162
00:07:39,533 --> 00:07:41,433
Friend, I'm sorry I'm busy.

163
00:07:41,567 --> 00:07:42,667
We have lots of patients.

164
00:07:42,800 --> 00:07:44,233
I'll come see you tomorrow.

165
00:07:44,367 --> 00:07:45,700
- Bye!
- Alice...

166
00:07:53,633 --> 00:07:54,900
Sweetie, this coming New Year.

167
00:07:55,033 --> 00:07:56,767
I'll go there this New Year.
Okay?

168
00:07:56,900 --> 00:07:58,067
I already have a visa, sweetie.

169
00:07:58,467 --> 00:07:59,500
Really?

170
00:07:59,633 --> 00:08:02,167
Yes, sweetie. I applied
for a visa when you left.

171
00:08:02,300 --> 00:08:05,933
Because I planned to come see
you. Look for you.

172
00:08:08,433 --> 00:08:09,433
Darn you.

173
00:08:10,233 --> 00:08:11,567
Why are you rejecting it?

174
00:08:12,167 --> 00:08:13,567
Jerk.

175
00:08:18,333 --> 00:08:20,800
I was just waiting

176
00:08:20,967 --> 00:08:22,833
for your whereabouts
from Colonel Sarabia.

177
00:08:25,067 --> 00:08:26,833
That's for sure.

178
00:08:26,967 --> 00:08:28,267
New Year.

179
00:08:28,400 --> 00:08:30,067
Mom and I will wait for you.

180
00:08:30,200 --> 00:08:32,867
That's really for sure, sweetie.

181
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:34,400
Jeff,

182
00:08:34,533 --> 00:08:35,600
we don't want to take up much
of your time,

183
00:08:35,733 --> 00:08:37,067
so you can celebrate.

184
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:38,700
Let's just call each other
again. Okay?

185
00:08:38,833 --> 00:08:40,133
See you in the New Year.

186
00:08:40,800 --> 00:08:43,500
Bye, Dad! I love you so much!
Merry Christmas!

187
00:08:43,633 --> 00:08:45,500
Merry Christmas.

188
00:08:45,633 --> 00:08:46,733
Thank you.

189
00:08:46,867 --> 00:08:48,267
Merry Christmas.

190
00:08:50,467 --> 00:08:52,667
Mom, I'm finally going
to see Daisy.

191
00:09:01,733 --> 00:09:03,967
Why were you rejecting my calls?
Where did you go?

192
00:09:04,100 --> 00:09:05,133
Hey!

193
00:09:06,300 --> 00:09:07,867
What's wrong? What happened?

194
00:09:10,533 --> 00:09:11,833
I came from Felma's house.

195
00:09:15,800 --> 00:09:17,600
They were so happy.

196
00:09:19,167 --> 00:09:20,933
While we're broken.

197
00:09:22,367 --> 00:09:23,767
I can't let that happen, Hazel.

198
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:26,633
They're whole now.

199
00:09:27,800 --> 00:09:31,967
And we'll never be
with our only child,

200
00:09:32,733 --> 00:09:36,100
all because of them.

201
00:09:38,500 --> 00:09:40,033
I won't stop this now.

202
00:09:41,133 --> 00:09:43,233
I can't stand seeing...

203
00:09:44,533 --> 00:09:47,800
that monstrous family happy.

204
00:09:50,533 --> 00:09:52,500
When are you
planning to do it?

205
00:09:53,500 --> 00:09:54,933
Before the New Year.

206
00:09:59,367 --> 00:10:00,467
Who will you go after first?

207
00:10:02,200 --> 00:10:04,367
Who do you want to go first?

208
00:10:09,633 --> 00:10:10,833
I envy you, Jeff.

209
00:10:10,967 --> 00:10:13,633
You'll be with Tetay and Daisy.

210
00:10:13,767 --> 00:10:16,333
Call us right away
once you land.

211
00:10:16,467 --> 00:10:17,567
Call you right away?

212
00:10:17,700 --> 00:10:18,833
Can't I spend time with
my daughter and her mom first?

213
00:10:18,967 --> 00:10:20,800
So stingy.

214
00:10:20,933 --> 00:10:24,800
Don't keep Tetay
all to yourself.

215
00:10:25,567 --> 00:10:27,967
You'll be with her now.

216
00:10:28,833 --> 00:10:31,833
While all we have
is a video call.

217
00:10:32,967 --> 00:10:35,900
We'll get
your pocket money then.

218
00:10:36,067 --> 00:10:37,900
I was just kidding!
Come on, Mom!

219
00:10:38,033 --> 00:10:39,500
Once I land, as soon
as they pick me up,

220
00:10:39,633 --> 00:10:41,533
I video call you.
I'll call you right away.

221
00:10:43,800 --> 00:10:45,567
Coleen, Andrea,

222
00:10:45,967 --> 00:10:48,267
you take care of Mom and Dad
for now. Okay?

223
00:10:48,400 --> 00:10:49,600
While I'm away.

224
00:10:50,800 --> 00:10:51,700
They need you.

225
00:10:51,833 --> 00:10:52,900
You've become serious
all of a sudden, huh?

226
00:10:53,033 --> 00:10:55,233
It's as if you'll
be gone for so long.

227
00:10:55,367 --> 00:10:56,967
Are you working overseas?

228
00:10:57,100 --> 00:10:59,300
You'll just stay there
for two weeks, bro!

229
00:10:59,433 --> 00:11:01,200
You talk too much! Come here.

230
00:11:01,333 --> 00:11:04,667
Come, sweetie.
Come here. Come here.

231
00:11:04,800 --> 00:11:06,000
Be safe, okay?

232
00:11:06,133 --> 00:11:08,400
Be safe.
A kangaroo might kick you.

233
00:11:08,567 --> 00:11:09,733
Oh, yeah.

234
00:11:12,533 --> 00:11:14,167
Dad.

235
00:11:14,300 --> 00:11:15,633
Be safe, okay?

236
00:11:15,767 --> 00:11:16,933
I'll get going now.

237
00:11:17,067 --> 00:11:17,900
- Thank you.
- Bye!

238
00:11:18,033 --> 00:11:19,133
- Oh, my bag!
- Jeff!

239
00:11:19,267 --> 00:11:21,133
Haven't I hugged you yet?

240
00:11:21,267 --> 00:11:22,333
Maybe it would be better
if I don't.

241
00:11:22,467 --> 00:11:23,567
You should hug me, too.

242
00:11:23,700 --> 00:11:27,333
- Of course.
- It's okay.

243
00:11:27,467 --> 00:11:28,533
I'll miss you.

244
00:11:28,667 --> 00:11:31,700
I'm sorry
if I'm being emotional.

245
00:11:31,833 --> 00:11:33,733
It seems that we're not
seeing each other again.

246
00:11:33,867 --> 00:11:34,867
Oh, wait.

247
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:36,200
Here.

248
00:11:36,333 --> 00:11:38,367
Please deliver my love letter
to your daughter and her mom.

249
00:11:38,500 --> 00:11:39,667
Why do you have
a love letter?

250
00:11:39,800 --> 00:11:41,300
- That's for Daisy and Tetay.
- Wait, I'll read it first.

251
00:11:41,467 --> 00:11:42,933
I'm afraid
of what you wrote in here.

252
00:11:43,067 --> 00:11:44,433
Of course, I miss them.

253
00:11:44,567 --> 00:11:45,833
How are you, guys? I miss you.

254
00:11:45,967 --> 00:11:47,633
Please come home
to the Philippines.

255
00:11:47,767 --> 00:11:49,300
See? Of course,
I miss them so much.

256
00:11:49,433 --> 00:11:50,133
There's more.

257
00:11:50,267 --> 00:11:52,233
What's this?

258
00:11:52,367 --> 00:11:53,767
A foot!

259
00:11:54,400 --> 00:11:55,267
Why is there a foot here?

260
00:11:55,400 --> 00:11:58,200
They might want to know my size.

261
00:11:58,333 --> 00:12:00,533
It's size 7, Didang!

262
00:12:00,667 --> 00:12:01,567
Just the right shoe, okay?

263
00:12:01,700 --> 00:12:02,800
You didn't include
the left one.

264
00:12:02,933 --> 00:12:03,800
The other one is size 9.

265
00:12:03,933 --> 00:12:05,333
It's swollen.

266
00:12:05,467 --> 00:12:07,100
Just give it to them.

267
00:12:07,233 --> 00:12:08,900
Come on. I'll miss all of you.

268
00:12:09,033 --> 00:12:10,467
I'll miss you.

269
00:12:10,600 --> 00:12:12,167
Thank you, Mom and Dad.

270
00:12:13,833 --> 00:12:15,267
I think I want a hug.

271
00:12:16,300 --> 00:12:18,200
Come on. I'll miss you.
I'll come back soon.

272
00:12:18,333 --> 00:12:20,133
I'll come back.

273
00:12:20,267 --> 00:12:21,400
Didang, don't.

274
00:12:23,333 --> 00:12:25,700
I'll remember your scent, bro.

275
00:12:25,833 --> 00:12:27,333
- Why?
- And your voice.

276
00:12:27,467 --> 00:12:28,800
Hey!

277
00:12:28,933 --> 00:12:30,300
It's just two weeks.

278
00:12:33,400 --> 00:12:35,667
Mom, don't worry.

279
00:12:35,800 --> 00:12:38,267
For sure, Coleen's
already on the way home.

280
00:12:38,400 --> 00:12:39,367
She's almost here.

281
00:12:39,500 --> 00:12:41,633
Rona and their friends
are with her.

282
00:12:41,767 --> 00:12:43,800
They'll bring her here.

283
00:12:43,933 --> 00:12:45,200
She said

284
00:12:45,867 --> 00:12:47,200
she'd be home by 6:00

285
00:12:48,967 --> 00:12:51,033
It's already 7:30.

286
00:12:51,633 --> 00:12:53,333
Why didn't she call?

287
00:12:53,867 --> 00:12:57,133
She should at least
answer the call.

288
00:12:57,267 --> 00:12:59,733
Where's her location?
I'll go pick her up.

289
00:12:59,867 --> 00:13:01,567
No, Joel.

290
00:13:02,033 --> 00:13:03,767
I'll call her again.

291
00:13:05,133 --> 00:13:06,633
It's ringing.

292
00:13:07,467 --> 00:13:11,633
Mom, I'm sorry
I couldn't answer your call.

293
00:13:11,767 --> 00:13:14,100
Rona and I
had been busy chatting.

294
00:13:14,233 --> 00:13:17,400
We just separated ways.
But I'm almost at the village.

295
00:13:18,433 --> 00:13:21,467
Coleen, you
should've told Mom.

296
00:13:21,633 --> 00:13:23,333
We were worried about you.

297
00:13:23,467 --> 00:13:25,200
Sorry, sis.

298
00:13:25,333 --> 00:13:27,133
This won't happen again.

299
00:13:27,267 --> 00:13:28,833
Coleen, where are you exactly
now?

300
00:13:28,967 --> 00:13:29,867
I'll come pick you up.

301
00:13:30,500 --> 00:13:31,733
No need, bro.

302
00:13:31,867 --> 00:13:35,933
I'm just three streets away
from the village's gate.

303
00:13:36,633 --> 00:13:38,000
Okay, dear. Be safe.

304
00:13:38,133 --> 00:13:41,400
Hurry so you can still
join us for dinner.

305
00:13:41,533 --> 00:13:42,767
Mom...

306
00:13:42,900 --> 00:13:43,900
Dad...

307
00:13:46,033 --> 00:13:48,933
I feel like someone's
following me.

308
00:13:49,067 --> 00:13:49,933
Are you sure?

309
00:13:50,067 --> 00:13:51,167
Coleen, run!

310
00:13:51,300 --> 00:13:52,800
Which street are you on?

311
00:13:52,933 --> 00:13:54,233
I'm on Zamora.

312
00:13:54,400 --> 00:13:57,200
- Coleen, be safe.
- I'll go to her.

313
00:13:59,100 --> 00:14:00,400
Sweetie.

314
00:14:02,133 --> 00:14:04,233
Mom, Dad, please help me.

315
00:14:04,367 --> 00:14:09,267
Help!

316
00:14:10,400 --> 00:14:12,167
Please help me!

317
00:15:03,800 --> 00:15:04,900
He's gone. He's gone.

318
00:15:05,033 --> 00:15:07,933
- Jojo.
- Hush now. He's gone, okay?

319
00:15:22,833 --> 00:15:24,733
I was at the convenience store.

320
00:15:24,867 --> 00:15:27,067
I saw a man running.

321
00:15:27,200 --> 00:15:29,067
Like he was after someone.

322
00:15:29,900 --> 00:15:31,267
And I saw Coleen.

323
00:15:31,800 --> 00:15:34,467
So I had a feeling.
And followed them.

324
00:15:35,333 --> 00:15:37,233
What does the man look like?

325
00:15:37,600 --> 00:15:39,200
I didn't notice.

326
00:15:39,333 --> 00:15:40,600
He covered his face
with a hoodie.

327
00:15:41,267 --> 00:15:42,933
I couldn't see it.

328
00:15:43,400 --> 00:15:46,267
I'm glad you were there, Jojo.
You were able to follow them.

329
00:15:46,400 --> 00:15:47,200
Thank you.

330
00:15:48,167 --> 00:15:51,200
Thank you so much, Jojo.

331
00:15:52,167 --> 00:15:54,100
if not for you,

332
00:15:55,133 --> 00:15:57,700
Coleen could've been
in danger

333
00:15:59,467 --> 00:16:00,900
My hero.

334
00:16:01,033 --> 00:16:03,233
My knight in shining armor.

335
00:16:03,367 --> 00:16:05,533
My prince charming!

336
00:16:06,933 --> 00:16:09,833
Didang. She didn't save you.

337
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:11,667
It was Coleen. Right?
This is her moment.

338
00:16:11,800 --> 00:16:12,800
Sorry.

339
00:16:13,567 --> 00:16:15,500
Who could that man be?

340
00:16:17,667 --> 00:16:23,600
Do you have a suitor
you're not telling us, Coleen?

341
00:16:23,733 --> 00:16:26,033
I don't, sis.

342
00:16:28,333 --> 00:16:29,200
Could he be...

343
00:16:29,833 --> 00:16:32,433
a snatcher or hold upper?

344
00:16:33,333 --> 00:16:35,933
Maybe our...

345
00:16:37,633 --> 00:16:38,733
enemy is behind this.

346
00:16:39,767 --> 00:16:40,767
Hazel.

347
00:16:46,467 --> 00:16:48,267
The nerve of them
to call me an enemy.

348
00:16:48,400 --> 00:16:50,333
They're the ones who
keep getting after me.

349
00:16:53,100 --> 00:16:55,500
If you only saw Felma's face...

350
00:16:57,433 --> 00:17:00,367
You could see her fear
for her child.

351
00:17:00,500 --> 00:17:01,433
Good!

352
00:17:01,567 --> 00:17:03,433
That's what we want, right?

353
00:17:04,100 --> 00:17:05,500
Scare them.

354
00:17:05,633 --> 00:17:07,833
Emotional torture.

355
00:17:07,967 --> 00:17:09,267
And let it build up.

356
00:17:09,400 --> 00:17:11,233
Until she goes through
the same thing I went through

357
00:17:11,367 --> 00:17:12,733
when Jessica died.

358
00:17:13,667 --> 00:17:16,667
I can't forgive them
for the pain I feel

359
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:21,333
for not meeting our child.

360
00:17:23,433 --> 00:17:25,033
I will never forgive them.

361
00:17:26,067 --> 00:17:28,700
So keep on earning
their trust.

362
00:17:30,067 --> 00:17:32,000
When the perfect
time comes...

363
00:17:32,733 --> 00:17:36,333
We'll make a move
when they least expect it.

364
00:17:42,100 --> 00:17:43,333
Hello, Joel?

365
00:17:43,467 --> 00:17:46,567
I'm already outside FMP.
I'll wait for you here.

366
00:17:46,700 --> 00:17:47,567
Be safe.

367
00:17:50,600 --> 00:17:51,667
She's pretty, bro.

368
00:17:54,200 --> 00:17:55,633
Hi, Miss Beautiful.

369
00:17:55,767 --> 00:17:57,100
- Come with us.
- Stop.

370
00:17:57,233 --> 00:17:58,333
- Stay away.
- Come on.

371
00:17:58,467 --> 00:17:59,700
Let's go!

372
00:18:01,667 --> 00:18:02,833
Pervert!

373
00:18:06,767 --> 00:18:07,633
Come here!

374
00:18:07,767 --> 00:18:08,867
- Come here!
- Let go of me!

375
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:11,867
- Come with us!
- Let go of me!

376
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:12,567
Let go of me!

377
00:18:13,400 --> 00:18:14,733
You're still going to fight me,
huh!

378
00:18:14,867 --> 00:18:16,833
Let go of me! Pervert!

379
00:18:17,433 --> 00:18:18,267
Help!

380
00:18:18,400 --> 00:18:19,500
You, jerk!

381
00:18:28,633 --> 00:18:29,700
You, bastard!

382
00:18:29,833 --> 00:18:31,967
Come here!

383
00:18:34,633 --> 00:18:35,867
Joel, that's enough!

384
00:18:36,500 --> 00:18:37,767
Stop it.

385
00:18:37,900 --> 00:18:39,400
What now? You, bastard!

386
00:18:39,533 --> 00:18:40,400
Stop!

387
00:18:40,533 --> 00:18:42,800
- Joel, let's go!
- What now?

388
00:18:42,933 --> 00:18:44,600
- Bastard!
- Pervert!

389
00:18:46,233 --> 00:18:48,133
Are you okay?

390
00:18:48,267 --> 00:18:50,600
- I'm okay now.
- You okay?

391
00:18:50,967 --> 00:18:52,600
Are you hurt?

392
00:18:53,567 --> 00:18:55,667
Sorry. Sorry, Andrea.

393
00:18:58,400 --> 00:18:59,767
It's okay.
That's enough.

394
00:19:02,400 --> 00:19:03,267
What's that about?

395
00:19:03,400 --> 00:19:05,500
Are they just messing
with a woman?

396
00:19:06,900 --> 00:19:09,467
What if it happens
to their moms?

397
00:19:10,300 --> 00:19:14,067
To their sisters? Grandmothers?
What would they feel?

398
00:19:14,200 --> 00:19:15,967
I'm so mad,
I could smash their faces.

399
00:19:17,033 --> 00:19:18,233
This is my fault.

400
00:19:18,867 --> 00:19:20,433
If I didn't get stuck
in traffic...

401
00:19:20,733 --> 00:19:22,133
If I were able to pick you
up sooner,

402
00:19:22,267 --> 00:19:24,500
those perverts
wouldn't have come near you.

403
00:19:27,267 --> 00:19:28,233
That's enough, Joel.

404
00:19:29,667 --> 00:19:31,133
I'm okay now.

405
00:19:31,267 --> 00:19:33,400
What I did to them
wasn't enough, Andrea.

406
00:19:34,400 --> 00:19:37,400
I'll smash their faces
if I see them again.

407
00:19:37,533 --> 00:19:40,067
I'll smash their faces.

408
00:19:40,200 --> 00:19:42,000
They'll regret
what they did to you.

409
00:19:45,200 --> 00:19:46,633
That's enough, Joel.

410
00:19:48,567 --> 00:19:50,833
Maybe we should
just let this slide.

411
00:19:52,733 --> 00:19:55,433
We can't let this slide.
What if...

412
00:19:57,467 --> 00:19:59,233
What if they didn't
just touch you?

413
00:19:59,367 --> 00:20:01,033
What if they took you?

414
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:03,000
Molested you? What if...

415
00:20:08,433 --> 00:20:11,200
I will never let anything
happen to you.

416
00:20:13,067 --> 00:20:14,700
I might end up
killing someone.

417
00:20:15,367 --> 00:20:16,733
Joel...

418
00:20:17,867 --> 00:20:18,867
don't be mad.

419
00:20:19,467 --> 00:20:20,767
Calm down now.

420
00:20:24,367 --> 00:20:25,500
You know...

421
00:20:27,867 --> 00:20:29,667
I want to thank you.

422
00:20:32,067 --> 00:20:34,767
Thank you for always saving me.

423
00:20:36,367 --> 00:20:38,167
For always helping me.

424
00:20:42,833 --> 00:20:46,533
Thank you for everything
you do for me.

425
00:21:03,500 --> 00:21:04,733
What do you think of me?

426
00:21:04,867 --> 00:21:06,700
Hiding tons of cash
in a suitcase?

427
00:21:06,833 --> 00:21:07,800
Of course not.

428
00:21:07,933 --> 00:21:10,467
Whatever I gave you,
that's it. Bye.

429
00:21:13,267 --> 00:21:14,500
This Anton guy is so annoying.

430
00:21:14,633 --> 00:21:16,867
He was asking
for additional pay.

431
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:19,400
Is it my fault that he let
himself get beaten up by Joel?

432
00:21:19,533 --> 00:21:20,700
They're so stupid.

433
00:21:22,700 --> 00:21:25,033
At least they were able to do
the job.

434
00:21:25,767 --> 00:21:27,400
Two of their children
were victimized.

435
00:21:28,900 --> 00:21:31,033
This will definitely be
another blow to Felma

436
00:21:31,167 --> 00:21:32,867
and to my bastard husband.

437
00:21:33,367 --> 00:21:34,367
Serves them right.

438
00:21:37,533 --> 00:21:39,433
Just recently, it was Coleen.

439
00:21:40,400 --> 00:21:42,633
Now it's you.

440
00:21:43,300 --> 00:21:46,233
Bad people are everywhere now.

441
00:21:46,367 --> 00:21:48,067
Did they hurt you, Andeng?

442
00:21:48,200 --> 00:21:49,267
No, Dad.

443
00:21:49,400 --> 00:21:52,833
I'm okay.
Try not to get so affected.

444
00:21:52,967 --> 00:21:54,900
It might worsen your condition.

445
00:21:55,033 --> 00:21:58,133
You should've reported it
to the police.

446
00:21:58,267 --> 00:22:00,433
We just came from the precinct.

447
00:22:00,567 --> 00:22:02,800
We've already filed
a police report against them.

448
00:22:02,933 --> 00:22:04,133
Where are you now?

449
00:22:04,267 --> 00:22:06,100
We just dropped by the hospital,
Dad.

450
00:22:06,400 --> 00:22:07,667
We'll buy Mom's medicine.

451
00:22:07,800 --> 00:22:09,733
This is the only place
we can get it, remember?

452
00:22:09,867 --> 00:22:11,567
Okay, okay. Hurry up.

453
00:22:11,700 --> 00:22:14,933
Joel, please take care
of our Andeng.

454
00:22:15,100 --> 00:22:19,333
Yes, Uncle.
I'll take care of my Andeng.

455
00:22:19,467 --> 00:22:20,633
I didn't say anything.

456
00:22:20,767 --> 00:22:22,233
Okay. Bye, Mom and Dad.

457
00:22:22,367 --> 00:22:23,133
Bye.

458
00:22:25,533 --> 00:22:27,333
You're talking nonsense.

459
00:22:57,533 --> 00:22:59,633
Andrea. You go to the car first.

460
00:22:59,767 --> 00:23:00,700
I'll just use the restroom.

461
00:23:01,333 --> 00:23:02,267
- Okay. I'll wait for you.
- I'll follow.

462
00:23:02,400 --> 00:23:03,700
Be safe, okay?

463
00:23:07,933 --> 00:23:09,200
Excuse me.

464
00:23:22,633 --> 00:23:23,833
That's not enough.

465
00:23:23,967 --> 00:23:24,833
Whatever.

466
00:23:25,467 --> 00:23:29,100
Just wait for my orders.

467
00:23:34,467 --> 00:23:36,267
We can't just settle for that.

468
00:23:37,367 --> 00:23:39,100
Who is she talking to?

469
00:23:40,933 --> 00:23:42,400
Since you're there,

470
00:23:42,767 --> 00:23:46,033
think of what you can do
to Jeffrey.

471
00:24:02,433 --> 00:24:04,267
Hey!

472
00:24:10,533 --> 00:24:11,867
What are you going to do
with that?

473
00:24:12,600 --> 00:24:13,433
Enough said.

474
00:24:13,567 --> 00:24:14,633
Why isn't he picking up?

475
00:24:14,867 --> 00:24:16,267
Why did he send this to me?

476
00:24:16,400 --> 00:24:18,467
Excuse me.
Where are the restrooms?

477
00:24:18,600 --> 00:24:20,100
Ma'am? Sir?

478
00:24:21,133 --> 00:24:22,333
Joel?

479
00:24:22,900 --> 00:24:23,967
Joel.

480
00:24:25,033 --> 00:24:25,767
Hazel,

481
00:24:26,833 --> 00:24:28,533
did you do that to Joel?

482
00:24:28,700 --> 00:24:31,600
I'm sorry, Joel.
I didn't mean to do that.

483
00:24:31,733 --> 00:24:34,767
But you all brace yourselves.
Because I'm not going to stop.
